          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "REDUC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The  method  based  on the method of reduction",
                " was used  for  the  evaluation  of  the  photonuclear",
                " reaction   cross   sections  -  the  most  reasonably",
                " achievable monoenergetic   representations   of   the",
                " information about  reaction  cross  section  obtained",
                " using bremsstrahlung.",
                "The evaluation  method  consists  of  using  the  real",
                " apparatus function  (effective  photon  spectrum)  of",
                " each  individual  experiment  to reduce the data to a",
                " representation generated by an apparatus function  of",
                " better   quality.   The  most  reasonably  achievable",
                " monoenergetic representation of the information about",
                " cross   section  contained  in  different  experiment",
                " observables was   obtained   for  gaussian  apparatus",
                " functions with various energy resolutions."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "  Mean root-square  errors are given."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The photodisintegration    reaction    34S(g,sn)   and",
                " photofission reaction   232Th(g,f)   cross   sections",
                " intermediate structure  has  been  investigated.  The",
                " energy  dependencies  of  the  34S[(g,n)  +  (g,np) +",
                " (g,2n)]  reaction  cross  section  for  the   initial",
                " g-quanta  energies  Eg  =  10 - 28 MeV and 232Th(g,f)",
                " reaction cross section for Eg = 4.8 -  8.9  MeV  have",
                " been  evaluated using the new advanced version of the",
                " method of reduction.  The  reduction  models  of  the",
                " uncertainty    minimization    and    of   additional",
                " information  have  been  used  correspondingly.   The",
                " 34S(g,sn) reaction  cross  section  has been obtained",
                " for energy resolution of about  200  -  300  keV  and",
                " statistical  uncertainty ~ 5 - 10 %  and 232Th(g,f) -",
                " for correspondingly 75 keV and ~ 8 - 14 %."
              ]
            }
          ],
